## 2. API Layer & Backend Integration [HIGH]

Keep the API layer **modular and separate** from UI. Structure for external backends (e.g. NestJS, Supabase). A Backend like convex; follow the convex recommended structure:

```
services/
  api/
    client.ts      # Base HTTP client, auth headers, interceptors
    endpoints.ts   # Centralized endpoint constants
  user.service.ts  # User-related API calls
  auth.service.ts  # Auth-related API calls
```

**Base client** – Single place for base URL, auth, error handling:

```typescript
// services/api/client.ts
import * as SecureStore from 'expo-secure-store';

const BASE_URL = process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL;

/** Base fetch wrapper with auth and error handling */
export async function apiClient<T>(
  path: string,
  options?: RequestInit
): Promise<T> {
  const token = await SecureStore.getItemAsync('token');
  const res = await fetch(`${BASE_URL}${path}`, {
    ...options,
    headers: {
      'Content-Type': 'application/json',
      ...(token && { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` }),
      ...options?.headers,
    },
  });
  if (!res.ok) {
    if (res.status === 401) {
      await refreshTokenOrLogout();
    }
    throw new Error(`API ${res.status}: ${await res.text()}`);
  }
  return res.json();
}
```

**401 / token refresh** – On 401, refresh token via auth service or clear storage and redirect to login. Centralize this in the client.

**Service modules** – One file per domain, typed responses:

```typescript
// services/user.service.ts
import { apiClient } from '@/services/api/client';

/** Fetches user by ID. Used by useUser and prefetch. */
export async function fetchUser(id: string) {
  return apiClient<User>(`/users/${id}`);
}
```

**Documentation** – Brief JSDoc on public service functions and API client helpers. No inline comments for obvious code.

