## 3. Prefer Expo SDKs

Use **Expo SDK packages** over third-party alternatives. Install via: `npx expo install <package>`

| Need | Use Expo | Avoid |
|------|----------|-------|
| Images | `expo-image` | `Image` from react-native |
| Secure storage | `expo-secure-store` | AsyncStorage for secrets |
| Env/config | `expo-constants` | Hardcoded config |
| Biometrics | `expo-local-authentication` | Third-party auth libs |
| Linking/URLs | `expo-linking` | react-native Linking |
| File system | `expo-file-system` | react-native-fs |
| Updates | `expo-updates` | Custom OTA logic |
| Splash | `expo-splash-screen` | Custom splash |
| Fonts | `expo-font` | Manual font linking, third-party font libs |
| Network status | `expo-network` | Custom polling, manual fetch checks |

Expo SDKs are maintained with the Expo release cycle and work in Expo Go / dev builds.

