## 6. Memoization & Lists [CRITICAL]

- **useMemo** – Expensive computations or when referential equality matters.
- **useCallback** – Callbacks passed to memoized children or in dependency arrays.
- **React.memo** – Pure components that re-render often with same props.
- **Lists** – Use virtualized lists, not `ScrollView` + `map`:

| Items | Use | Avoid |
|-------|-----|-------|
| < 20 static | ScrollView OK | — |
| 20–100 | FlatList | ScrollView + map |
| > 100 | FlashList (`@shopify/flash-list`) | FlatList, ScrollView |

**Quick pattern:**
```typescript
// ❌ BAD
<ScrollView>{items.map((i) => <Item key={i.id} {...i} />)}</ScrollView>

// ✅ GOOD
<FlashList data={items} renderItem={({ item }) => <Item {...item} />} estimatedItemSize={50} keyExtractor={(i) => i.id} />
```

**Common pitfalls:** Inline `renderItem` causes re-renders; use `useCallback` or define outside. FlashList requires `estimatedItemSize`.

